# Albany Parking Ticket Appeal — Cursor Project Rules

## What this app is
A production web app helping City of Albany, NY residents appeal parking
tickets. Express + Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui, built
into a single bundle. Deployed on Railway.

## Hard rules (non-negotiable)
- NEVER fabricate or hallucinate legal citations, statutes, deadlines, or
  ticket data. Every policy fact must trace to an official City of Albany
  source. If a fact can't be verified from a primary source, do not state it.
- The ticket lookup is a GUIDED HAND-OFF to the official portal
  (albany.rmcpay.com). That portal is WAF/CAPTCHA-protected — do NOT attempt
  to proxy, scrape, or bypass it. Collect plate+state, copy plate, open the
  official portal in a new tab.
- For external navigation inside iframes/cross-origin contexts, use a real
  <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">, never programmatic
  window.open (Safari blocks it via COOP).

## Architecture
- client/  — React frontend (single hash route, see src/pages/home.tsx)
- server/  — Express backend (routes.ts has the API endpoints)
- shared/  — shared types
- script/build.ts — build entry (produces dist/index.cjs + dist/public)

## API endpoints (server/routes.ts)
- GET  /api/health
- POST /api/extract-ticket  — optional OpenAI vision OCR; degrades gracefully
  to {ok:false, unavailable:true} when OPENAI_API_KEY is unset. Rate-limited.
- POST /api/suggest-situation — optional xAI (Grok) classifier: maps a
  plain-English description to one of the 8 curated situation ids. The model
  ONLY picks from that fixed list — it never generates legal content.
  Degrades gracefully when XAI_API_KEY is unset. Rate-limited.
- POST /api/polish-letter   — optional xAI (Grok) copy-edit of the generated
  letter. Prompt hard-forbids changing facts or adding/altering citations.
  Degrades gracefully when XAI_API_KEY is unset. Rate-limited.
- POST /api/submit-foil      — logs server-side; client completes via mailto.

## Env vars (all optional — see .env.example)
- PORT (Railway injects; don't set manually)
- OPENAI_API_KEY (enables photo auto-fill)
- OPENAI_VISION_MODEL (default: gpt-4o)
- XAI_API_KEY (enables situation matching + letter polish via api.x.ai)
- XAI_MODEL (default: grok-4.3)

## Commands
- npm install        # first time (node_modules not included in zip)
- npm run dev        # local dev on :5000
- npm run build      # production build
- npm start          # run production bundle
- npm run check      # tsc typecheck
